column15:
PG. 1 The healing guati ritual: The Baluchis describe this process in this way: A person (more often a woman) falls ill and the doctors cannot cure her....then as a last resort, she is taken to a specialist in the guat, a kind of Baluchi spirit. These spirits are of a particular species, much more stubborn than ordinary ones, and cannot be dealt with except by organizing a musical session...."

PG. 6 This sequence comes from the first part of a guati session. The shaman fell into trance, followed by its patient.

